"Vardar A., Kurtulmuş F., Darga A.","Local indications of climate changes in Turkey: Bursa as a case example",2011,"Climatic Change","106","2",,"255","266",,,10.1007/s10584-010-9904-8,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-79955028993&partnerID=40&md5=caea5afacf304c41569eaf53dd2ca3df","Department of Biosystems Engineering, Faculty of Agriculture, Uludaǧ University, 16059 Bursa, Turkey","Vardar, A., Department of Biosystems Engineering, Faculty of Agriculture, Uludaǧ University, 16059 Bursa, Turkey; Kurtulmuş, F., Department of Biosystems Engineering, Faculty of Agriculture, Uludaǧ University, 16059 Bursa, Turkey; Darga, A., Department of Biosystems Engineering, Faculty of Agriculture, Uludaǧ University, 16059 Bursa, Turkey","This study aims to put out on what ratio Bursa province, one of the important heavy industry regions of Turkey, has been affected climatic process called ""Global Warming"" or ""Climate Change"". For this intend climatic measurement results from Bursa center, top of Uludaǧ Mount, Yenişehir and Keles meteorological stations were used. These measurements were taken as minimum temperature at night-time, maximum temperature at day-time, and mean temperature, mean pressure, insolation intensity, insolation duration, mean wind speed, minimum temperature above soil, soil temperatures at depths of 5, 10, and 20 cm rainfall. Overall, our statistical results showed that there was a considerable warming at statistically 1% and 5% levels in summer months, particularly in July Almost all performed measurements confirm this result. According to climatic data for thirty years (1975-2005), in the last twelve years contrary to previous 18 years, mean temperature values were higher than long-term mean value nine times (years) repetitively. Temperatures did not deviated higher than 0. 5°C in six of these. At the temperatures below mean, The maximum deviation was -0. 4°C. © 2010 Springer Science+Business Media B.V.",,"Climatic data; Climatic process; Heavy industries; Maximum temperature; Mean pressures; Mean temperature; Mean values; Mean wind speed; Measurement results; Meteorological station; Soil temperature; Summer months; Global warming; Incident solar radiation; Optimization; climate change; industrial location; rainfall; soil temperature; temperature effect; wind velocity; Bursa [Turkey]; Turkey",,,,,,"Brown, L.R., Plan B 3. 0 Uygarli{dotless}ǧi{dotless} Kurtarmak için Harekete Geçmek. Earth Policy Institute, w. w. Norton& Company, Newyork (Türkçe çeviri: Ayşe Başçi{dotless} Tema Vakfi{dotless} Yayi{dotless}nlari{dotless} İstanbul); Caseldine, C., Langdon, P., Holmes, N., Early Holocene climate variability and the timing and extent of the Holocene theremal maximum (HTM) in northern Iceland (2006) Quat Sci Rev, 25, pp. 2314-2331; Caseldine, C., Langdon, P., Holmes, N., Early Holocene climate variability and the timing and extent of the Holocene theremal maximum (HTM) in northern Iceland (2006) Quat Sci Rev, 25, pp. 2314-2331; Churkina, G., Brovkin, V., von Bloh, W., Trusilova, K., Jung, M., Dentener, F., Synergy of rising nitrogen depositions and atmospheric CO2 on land carbon uptake moderately offsets global warming (2009) Glob Biogeochem Cycles, 23, p. 4027. , doi:10.1029/2008GB003291; Clover, C., Thin ice alert by polar scientists (1989) Daily Telegraph; Coghlan, A., American Navy witholds greenhouse data (1989) New Scientist, p. 46; Dirican, M., Yukari{dotless}da Neler Oluyor (1997) Bilim Ve Teknik Dergisi Sayi{dotless}, 355, pp. 32-39; (2006) DMI TC Devlet Meteoroloji İşleri Genel Müdürlüǧü, Ankara; (2009), http://earth.google.com, Google EarthIDKK İklim Deǧişikliǧinin Etkilerinin Araşti{dotless}ri{dotless}lmasi{dotless} Çali{dotless}şma Grubu Raporu (2004) Çevre ve Orman Bakanli{dotless}ǧi{dotless} Devlet Meteoroloji İşleri Genel Müdürlüǧü, Ankara; Report to IPCC from working group 1: Policymakers' summary of the scientific assessment of climate change (1990) Intergovernmental panel on climate change